\section{Roles and Responsibilities}

While the following roles are required to operate the test efficiently, personnel constraints will limit the amount of these roles that will be on the boat for deployment. The rest of the testing personel shall attend to the pilots and observe the test remotely from the mission control center.
\begin{enumerate}

    \item \makebox[.5in]{\hrulefill} \textbf{Field Overseer:} Oversees and assists with the field test to ensure proper following of testing procedures, as well as provide a first hand account of the field test. This is the only personnel 100\% required to be on the boat for the test to be carried out.
    
    \item \makebox[.5in]{\hrulefill} \textbf{Videographer:} Collects photographic and video data for later analysis using camera of choice. This role can be carried out by the field overseer for the boat operation, as well as an individual assigned to mission control for the piloting portion. 
    
    \item \makebox[.5in]{\hrulefill} \textbf{Test Lead:} Coordinates with SSC and organizes Capstone members. This role has no locational requirement.
    
    \item \makebox[.5in]{\hrulefill} \textbf{Data Lead:} Collects Seaglider data from SSC team for analysis. This role will be filled by an individual at mission control. 
    
    \item \makebox[.5in]{\hrulefill} \textbf{Test Members:} Any Capstone members assisting with or observing test
    
\end{enumerate}

