\subsection{Test Scenarios and Damage Modes}

\subsubsection{\textbf{Nominal (No Damage Modes/Fault Cases)}}
\begin{enumerate}
\item $100\%$ of wing and rudder attached
 
\end{enumerate}

\subsubsection{\textbf{Off Nominal (Damage Modes/Fault Cases)}}

\begin{enumerate}
    \item $50.0\%$ of port side wing span remaining 
    \item $0\%$ of top rudder span remaining 
\end{enumerate}



\subsubsection{\textbf{Test Dives}} All nominal and off nominal cases will perform this test dive procedure. The dive is to reflect a typical Seaglider operational dive set.


\begin{enumerate}
    \item Dive 1: 120 meter dive depth
    \item Dive 2: 120 meter dive depth
\end{enumerate}

All other dive input parameters are determined by the pilot in order to represent a typical Seaglider mission given these depths. For each dive, the mission parameters and inputs are to be recorded, tabulated, and kept consistent for each fault case undergoing this dive set. These dive depths can be changed upon SSC piloting discretion or recommendations.








